description: Associates a subnet in your VPC or an internet gateway or virtual private gateway attached to your VPC with a route table in your VPC. This association causes traffic from the subnet or gateway to be routed according to the routes in the route table. The action returns an association ID, which you need in order to disassociate the route table later. A route table can be associated with multiple subnets. For more information, see Route tables in the Amazon VPC User Guide.

parameters.name: RouteTableId
parameters.description: The ID of the route table.

nested_items.name: AssociationId
nested_items.description: The route table association ID. This ID is required for disassociating the route table.
